<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1504,2070]" box="[189,495,1504,1530]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,495,1504,1530]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Buxb." authorityName="Buxb." box="[263,490,1504,1530]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae Buxb.</taxonomicName>
:
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1504,2070]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
—The 
<taxonomicName box="[575,713,1504,1530]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae</taxonomicName>
had long been a heterogeneous group of South American genera (
<taxonomicName authority="Speg." authorityName="Speg." box="[145,306,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Parodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[145,236,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Parodia</emphasis>
Speg.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil." authorityName="Phil." box="[315,472,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,413,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eriosyce</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Werderm." authorityName="Werderm." box="[481,724,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Blossfeldia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[481,605,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Blossfeldia</emphasis>
Werderm.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" box="[732,989,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,816,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Frailea</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1107,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Copiapoa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[997,1107,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Copiapoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority=", Neowerdermannia Fric, and Austrocactus" authorityName="Neowerdermannia Fric, and Austrocactus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eulychnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1119,1233,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eulychnia</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1244,1451,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Neowerdermannia</emphasis>
Frič, and 
<emphasis box="[248,393,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Austrocactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R." box="[419,618,1576,1602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="312 - 326" refId="ref18317" refString="Nyffeler, R. (2002) Phylogenetic relationships in the Cactus family. American Journal of Botany 89: 312 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 89.2.312" type="journal article" year="2002">Nyffeler’s (2002)</bibRefCitation>
DNA-based study, however, showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1244,1576,1602]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1255,1317,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." pageId="9" pageNumber="88" refId="ref17156" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2006) The New Cactus Lexicon. DH Books, Milborn Port, 526 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[1392,1452,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
is highly polyphyletic and, therefore, he reduced the tribe to the strongly supported monophyletic group (“core 
<taxonomicName box="[136,279,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae</taxonomicName>
”) comprising 
<emphasis box="[439,577,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName box="[439,537,1649,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Eriosyce</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[545,577,1648,1674]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Speg." authorityName="Speg." box="[593,755,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Parodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[593,684,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Parodia</emphasis>
Speg.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[763,795,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,795,1648,1674]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[859,1066,1648,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Neowerdermannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[859,1066,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Neowerdermannia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[1082,1358,1648,1674]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010)</bibRefCitation>
showed that the two monotypic genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Mottram" authorityName="Mottram" box="[498,736,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rimacactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,629,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Rimacactus</emphasis>
Mottram
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiesling &amp; Pilz" authorityName="Kiesling &amp; Pilz" box="[796,1050,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Yavia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[796,857,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Yavia</emphasis>
Kiesling &amp; Pilz
</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1287,1685,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1287,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eriosyce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1303,1394,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Parodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1303,1394,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Parodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[136,343,1720,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Neowerdermannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,343,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Neowerdermannia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, form a strongly supported monophyletic clade (“ 
<taxonomicName box="[901,1051,1720,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae</taxonomicName>
”). Finally, the results of 
<collectingRegion box="[1323,1424,1720,1746]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2019) corroborated the monophyly of the tribe, yet 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[748,945,1756,1782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" refId="ref17187" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2013) The New Cactus Lexicon, Atlas of Illustrations. Dh Books, Milborn Port, 373 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[810,865,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
upheld the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Werderm." authorityName="Werderm." box="[1211,1452,1756,1782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Blossfeldia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1335,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Blossfeldia</emphasis>
Werderm.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" box="[183,446,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Frailea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,267,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Frailea</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose
</taxonomicName>
within tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[590,732,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Notocacteae">Notocacteae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
